<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,356,484]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
REDESCRIPTION: Shell pyramidal-fusiform, b/l 
<number box="[730,841,356,380]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" value="0.29000000000000004" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.28">0.28-0.30</number>
, with very high, acuminately orthoconoid spire (a/l 
<number box="[151,262,390,414]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" value="0.365" valueMax="0.38" valueMin="0.35">0.35-0.38</number>
), contracted base and narrowly elliptical aperture; rostrum tapering, terminally rounded, not indented, fasciole present but only weakly swollen; false umbilicus absent. Inner lip with a smooth, glossy callus, its edge adnate; outer lip thin, anal sinus shallowly U-shaped, [edge of lip damaged anteriorly].
</paragraph>
